WEBVTT

00:01.149 --> 00:02.549
<i>Previously on</i>
The Big Bang Theory...

00:03.266 --> 00:04.866
Sheldon, did you just figure out

00:04.868 --> 00:08.135
a method for synthesizing a new
stable super-heavy element?

00:08.257 --> 00:09.940
Did I?!

00:09.942 --> 00:11.208
Well, that can't be right.

00:11.210 --> 00:12.909
No one's ever done that before.

00:12.911 --> 00:14.377
Except me because I just did it!

00:14.379 --> 00:16.546
♪ Sheldon and his brain, yeah

00:16.548 --> 00:18.582
♪ Sheldon and his brain,
yeah! ♪

00:18.584 --> 00:20.950
I've made a horrible mistake.

00:20.952 --> 00:22.052
What are you talking about?

00:22.054 --> 00:24.787
This table,
it's in square centimeters

00:24.789 --> 00:26.806
I read it as square meters.

00:26.808 --> 00:28.258
You know what that means?

00:28.260 --> 00:30.844
That Americans can't handle
the metric system?

00:32.430 --> 00:36.266
Amy, I was off
by a factor of 10,000.

00:36.268 --> 00:38.685
But the Chinese team
found the element.

00:38.687 --> 00:39.653
Yeah, well, they shouldn't have.

00:39.655 --> 00:41.605
My calculations were wrong.

00:41.607 --> 00:43.573
The greatest scientific
achievement of my life

00:43.575 --> 00:45.308
is based on a blunder.

00:45.310 --> 00:46.610
I'm not a genius.

00:46.612 --> 00:47.944
I'm a fraud.

00:47.946 --> 00:50.113
You know, Sheldon,
in neuroscience,

00:50.115 --> 00:52.815
we're forever finding something
in one part of the brain

00:52.817 --> 00:54.284
that we thought was
someplace else.

00:54.286 --> 00:56.986
Oh, great, now I'm
worse than a fraud.

00:56.988 --> 00:59.155
I'm practically a biologist.
someplace else.

01:01.759 --> 01:04.260
This is <i>Science Friday.</i>
I'm Ira Flatow.

01:04.263 --> 01:07.597
My guest today is responsible
for the discovery of the first

01:07.599 --> 01:10.166
stable super-heavy element.

01:10.168 --> 01:11.685
Welcome, Dr. Sheldon Cooper.

01:11.687 --> 01:13.436
Thank you.

01:13.438 --> 01:15.021
Uh, the university
made me come here.

01:15.023 --> 01:16.506
I didn't want to.

01:17.325 --> 01:20.360
Uh, big fan of the show.

01:20.362 --> 01:23.346
So, I understand
that you actually discovered

01:23.348 --> 01:25.532
this element by mistake.

01:27.486 --> 01:29.319
Yes.

01:29.321 --> 01:32.372
And some people in the science
community are calling it

01:32.374 --> 01:34.357
"The Wonder Blunder."

01:34.359 --> 01:36.025
Who? Give me their names.

01:36.027 --> 01:37.911
I bet it's Wolowitz.

01:37.913 --> 01:40.297
It's just such
a fascinating story.

01:40.299 --> 01:41.831
Your calculations are way off,

01:41.833 --> 01:44.200
but they find
the element anyway.

01:44.202 --> 01:46.503
It's like misreading
a treasure map

01:46.505 --> 01:48.922
and still finding the treasure.

01:48.924 --> 01:50.924
Can we talk
about something else?

01:50.926 --> 01:53.510
Do you know that I yodel?

01:55.846 --> 01:57.230
That's interesting,
but this could be taking you

01:57.232 --> 01:59.983
down the path
toward a Nobel Prize.

01:59.985 --> 02:01.351
And in chemistry, no less.

02:01.353 --> 02:03.503
And wouldn't
that be unusual?

02:03.505 --> 02:05.855
Because you're a physicist.

02:05.857 --> 02:08.157
Yes, yes, I'd be a physicist
with a Nobel in chemistry.

02:08.160 --> 02:10.360
Everyone laugh
at the circus freak.

02:11.612 --> 02:14.164
You know, I don't need to sit
here and take this, Flatow.

02:14.166 --> 02:16.499
It is because of bullies
like you,

02:16.501 --> 02:18.201
every day
more and more Americans

02:18.203 --> 02:20.704
are making the switch
to television.

02:21.789 --> 02:25.425
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

02:25.427 --> 02:28.762
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

02:28.764 --> 02:30.397
♪ The Earth ban to cool

02:30.399 --> 02:32.932
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

02:32.934 --> 02:35.602
♪ We built the Wall
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

02:35.604 --> 02:38.271
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

02:38.273 --> 02:40.190
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

02:40.192 --> 02:42.142
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

02:42.149 --> 02:46.149
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Big Bang Theory 7x10 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Discovery Dissipation</font>
